  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Habitat and community risk management and climate change in Lomas de Carabayllo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a continuation of PER294. Building on the achievements of PER294, CIDAP will continue to strengthen the skills of women, men and young people in Lomas de Carabayllo, targeting 9 urban settlements. CIDAP&#x2019;s work will focus on DRR, including the food crisis, on climate change adaptation, youth environmental leadership and the conservation of Lomas de la Primavera in the context of the coronavirus pandemic, with an emphasis on food security. In addition, in the first year of the project, CIDAP will support environmental human rights defenders, who are threatened due to land invaders and land traffickers, developing a protocol for their support and documenting cases, to be used to advocate for their protection, and will provide some support to the &apos;ollas comunes&apos; which have been established in solidarity 12 urban settlements.</narrative>
  </description>
